Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

entry.title: Donald H. Bochkay (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that fighter pilot Donald H. Bochkay (pictured) shot down two jet-powered Messerschmitt Me 262s while flying a propeller-driven P-51 Mustang?

entry.title: Babe Ruth Bows Out (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Babe Ruth Bows Out marked the first time a sports-related image won the Pulitzer Prize for Photography?

entry.title: Mako Morino (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that voice actress Mako Morino played volleyball for 14 years, but gave up the goal of playing professionally after being assigned to the non-serving libero position?

entry.title: Avengers (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Kevin Feige first envisioned a shared universe featuring the Avengers in the mid-2000s?

entry.title: Richard Twine (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that sociologist Richard Twine has developed the concept of the "vegan killjoy" who challenges anthropocentrism by their mere presence?

entry.title: Nurture (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Porter Robinson chose the title Nurture for his second album due to its evocation of the word nature and as a reference to the nature versus nurture debate?

entry.title: Tish (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the documentary Tish uses sets from Ricky Gervais's sitcom After Life?

entry.title: Adelaida K. Semesi (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that scientist Adelaida K. Semesi was known as "mama mangroves" due to her specialist knowledge of their ecology?
